76561198176534477,Not Recommended,268540,29400906,Posted: 21 January,all,samonn2000,"Usually I’d review a game using three simple criteria: Quality of the Story,  game world and gameplay.  For this particular game I’ll ignore the story and the game world for the simple reason that I personally didn’t like either one. As for the gameplay, I really did try giving this game a fair chance, but some puzzles are seriously beyond unreasonably illogical.  One example would be having to go back to the prison cell after freeing Spot and burn away the hey to uncover one of the valves. There is just no logical reason whatsoever to do that.  Another example would be using Spot with the pearl pressing machine to create the “five spot form”.  In both examples and many other, I found that the game just doesn’t provide enough feedback to direct the player towards the proper solution.  Of course one could claim this is the general purpose of a point&click adventure – to point, click and combine anything with everything until something works. Personally When playing a Point&Click adventure, I prefer it to be more of a nicely flowing interactive story rather than a guessing game."
