,Recommended,268540,31389120,Posted: 27 April,all,Lunairetic,"Just finished this charming point-and-click adventure & I loved it!! I finished it in 2 nights and just under 12 hours, and did not have any issues clicking with the cursor to start my adventure. That bug seems to be fixed. :)What I loved:- The art style is gorgeous, and I loved the retro style animated cutscenes! I see that for some players this was a drawback, but not for me!! It gives the whole game a nostalgic storybook fantasy feel, which is a huge plus in my opinion. The music is also lovely, and suits the game perfectly!- I played this game with the English audio, and aside from some odd clipping in some early dialogue, I thought it was great! I see that many players are complaining that Sadwick's voice is annoying, & they suggest playing it with the German audio & English subtitles. I personally didn't find his voice irritating at all, and found all of the game's English voice work to be very quirky and reminiscent of all my favorite vintage cartoon shows. I think it is important to understand the spirit of the game (which seems to be a kind of homage to all of my favorite dated fantasy things) in order to appreciate the English audio's charm. But it is wonderful that the German language audio is an option, of course. :)- The puzzles are pretty challenging! I am usually complaining that puzzles in adventure games are a bit too easy, but this is not so in The Whispered World! The puzzle solutions are often not obvious at all, & *most* of the time I enjoyed the challenge. (will explain further below.)- The world is very quirky & charming, with lots of oddball characters who have lots of personality & provide some very strange tasks to complete! The Neverending Story/Labyrinth vibe is STRONG in this game, so if you like puzzle point-and-click adventure games and also loved those movies then you will probably love the Whispered World! :)- The story & characters were compelling. Not that I expected anything less from a Daedalic adventure, but still! :D  I was in a rush to get through the puzzles so I could see what happened next!- The ending. I did not expect the ending AT ALL. It was a pleasant surprise, and unexpectedly moving. I totally cried because I am a big softie.- I really loved the game's sense of humor as well. I laughed a lot playing this game.There is one aspect of The Whispered World however that was very irritating to me, and that is....SADWICK WALKS VERY SLOWLY!! Yes, you can double click to skip to the next area, but only as long as you can see the exit node, and many canvases were very big!! So before I could skip to the next location I would still have to wait for Sadwick to sloooowly plod along. This is especially frustrating when dealing with a challenging puzzle that has objectives all over the place. I ended up having to consult a guide a few times, which I *hate* doing, just to save me time walking from point A to point B over and over again trying to work a puzzle out so I could get on to enjoying the story!Overall though, I really enjoyed playing this game, & I absolutely recommend it! I'm playing its sequel 'Silence' next, & I can't wait!"
