76561198045003224,Recommended,268540,31313754,Posted: 23 April,all,dudeduderson,"TL;DR at the bottom.The Whispered World is an interesting game.FIRST THINGS FIRST:I played this game completely in German with English subtitles. This is because the game is originally in German, so German voice acting is stellar. The English dub has strange audio clipping and is much worse. It also makes the Protagonist almost unbearable to listen to. To anyone interested in playing this game, I would HIGHLY ADVISE PLAYING IT IN GERMAN (with English subs if you don’t speak German).Secondly, I didn’t have any problems with clicking or graphics. The game worked for me from the get-go.THE ACTUAL REVIEW:The Whispered World is a decent point and click with only a small handful of “What the heck am I supposed to do?” moments. The art style is amazing and really feels like you’re inside of an artist’s drawing book. The characters are interesting and the dialogue is often very funny. The music is PHENOMENAL. It puts you straight into the world. The story is interesting and easy to follow, nothing too convoluted. I would all-in-all recommend this game, despite its few flaws.TL;DR: I liked it. Play it in German with English subs."
