,Not Recommended,268540,35480265,Posted: 4 October,all,Hip Marion Moseby,Fairly tedious to play.
,Recommended,268540,29836614,Posted: 10 February,all,KyleKirkpatrick123,"I've played quite a few Casual Games in my time ranging from Adventure to Hidden Object to Match 3, and I must say, the Whispered World Special Edition, is one of the best I have played in a long time!!WARNING! REVIEW MIGHT CONTAIN SLIGHT SPOILERS, Nothing major though!!The game starts out with Sadwick, a 12 Year old depressed clown in a Fantasy World known as Silentia. He is asleep in a moving trailer and keeps having the same nightmare. The world is collapsing and there is a Blue Moon that keeps haunting Sadwick. When he wakes up from his nightmare, we are introduced to the action and get to start playing!GAMEPLAY & CONTROLS -This game is a 2D Side Scroller, where you almost exclusively use the mouse to move Sadwick around, talk to characters, pick up and use objects, combine objects, and bunch of other things! You also use ESC to access the Main Menu, Save/Load Screen, etc. and the Spacebar to show ""Hints"" (It just shows you what you can click on in the current scene.) For the most part the game controls quite well, everything is nice and fluid. By holding down the RMB (MB2) for about 1.5 seconds on an active area, a menu pops up where you can interact further with an item (You have an Eye for Looking closer at the item, a Mouth for talking or eating, and a Hand for picking an item up.) This works well as you are able to examine items in a game closely than most other games, and it's sometimes funny (or sad) to hear Sadwick's thoughts. There are a fair share of puzzles, and 4 Mini-Games (I'll get into that on the Difficulty Area) in this game. You'll get an Acheviment every-time you solve a Mini-Game, or you'll get one if you Skip them all!GRAPHICS & ART-STYLE -This game has amazing art and graphics! All of the scenes are hand-drawn and the animations are also hand-done. They look stunning and not something you see a whole lot anymore in games. One of the highest highlights of this game is its fantastic art-style! As far as Graphics go, for a game released in 2009/10 I say its aged pretty well! There are no Graphic Options (Basically what you get is what you get) and there is no Widescreen Mode and the Resolution does max out at a certain point. Somewhat disapointing since this game was released in 2010, however not a deal-breaker and something I am able to overlook. In my person opinion, I think you will not be disapointed by the way this game looks, in fact, I think you will be amazed!STORY -The story in this game is fantastic! It's very emotional at times and has amazing plot twists! Some of the most unexpected things happen during the storyline. There are a total of 4 Chapters in this game! It took me around 6 Hours to do the First Chapter since I was trying to get used to the gamplay, Chapter 2 took me around 3 hours, Chapter 3 around 2 1/2 hours, and Chapter 4 around 3 1/2 hours. Keep in mind I am usually slower at completing games. The story again is another amazing highlight of this game. I don't want to spoil anything though, so I won't go much else into this, but in my Personal Opinion I don't think you will be disapointed with the story. It is so gripping and keeps you on the edge of your seat for most of the adventure!DIFFICULTY -This game starts out pretty simple (Like most games) however it does get pretty challenging. Challenging to the point where I had the YouTube Walkthrough pulled up in case I needed it! I do consider myself an Expert at these types of games, however on some things I couldn't figure out, some made sense once I saw it and other made absolutely made no sense and you would only do it by purely guessing. Also, the Mini-Games are another story! I skipped every single one after attempting each one for about 10 minutes. There are 4 and there really isn't any ""Logic"" behind 3 of them. It's just guess and hope you are right. So I would mark this game down for it's poor puzzle design. Now, I don't want easy puzzles, but I don't want puzzles that are just random and don't have you show any logic to solve them. Other than the Mini-Games, there are random puzzles spread throughout the game and some can be solved by looking around at other areas again and searching through your inventory, and some (for most of you) would probably require you to look up the Walkthrough on YouTube to see how they did it. One downfall of this is the Difficulty, it's pretty brutal, however you will get thorugh it. It doesn't prevent me from reccomending this game! Like stated above, it took me around 16 Hours to complete this game for the first time. I am usually slower at completing games. For the average person I'd say it would take around 10-15 hours depending on your Skill Level.SOUNDTRACK -The Soundtrack for this is AMAZING! Some of the tracks can keep you on edge while playing while others are more mellow and relaxing to listen to. The greatest thing is this game comes with the complete soundtrack free of charge (You can find where your the Game Files are for this game > bonus > soundtrack.) It comes in .mp3 and .flac! It's $6.99 on iTunes and Amazon, and I was considering buying it until I found it in the game files (I wish they told you it came with it) so I'm telling you this now to prevent you from accidently buying it on iTunes or Amazon. Again, the Soundtrack is another reason to buy this game.ACTORS, DIALOGUE, & CHARACTERS -**NOTICE! I played this game using the English Voice Actor and English Subtitles!!**One thing most people criticized on was the Voice Actor for Sadwick in this game. Yes, I will admit it's not the best ever and he does sound whiney and depressed (which he is a ""Depressed Clown"" so I shouldn't be so surprised on that) however I don't think it's THAT bad. I personally think it's okay. If it absolutely bothers you, try using the German voice as I've heard that's better from other reviewers, with the English Subtitles. The Dialogue in this game is pretty good. However some of the language that they use I'm not 100% sure most 12 year olds would understand. Like I've kept saying, he is depressed, so he does hint certain things that would be suicidal at times and sometimes just down-right sad and makes you feel bad for him. Examples: ""Nothing here but a Deep-Dark shaft, much like my life;"" ""Nothing but a deep dark abyss. Don't do it Sadwick, stay away from the edge..."" Sadwick also uses the words ""D*mn"" and ""He*l"" a few times in this game. You will meet other characters throughout this game however usually you will only see them for only that Chapter and then once the chapter is over you won't see them again the rest of the game. There is one exception to that, however that would be spoiling part of the story so I will leave it out.FINAL THOUGHTS -It's an amazing game! I would totally reccomend it if you enjoy Casual or Adventure Games, enjoy 2D Side-Scroller type games, enjoy games with Emotional Stories, or enjoy Difficult Games (Again, don't let the difficulty detour you from buying the game. It's an amazing game and don't let my thoughts about the difficulty persaude you otherwise from buying it simply because of that reason...)I reccomend this game!!"
,Recommended,268540,19648984,"Posted: 12 December, 2015",all,<™[-=> Cookiez <=-]™>,"Yes, this is definitely a worthwhile game to play. I've enjoyed playing Daedalic Games all the time, from Rufus's ridiculous antics in Dapeonia to the heart-warming stories of the Treewalkers and Marquis.You'll find so much creativity in Daedalic games, from the description of the Memory Thieves to the beautiful artwork of the Multi-eyed Angler Fish (You'll have to find those things on your own).PROS1. Creative StorylineIt starts out extremely boring at the beginning but the story gets better as you progress. You'll find tons of interesting imaginatives scattered all over the place to keep you interested. Proper storytelling. E.g. Asgil (GILSA) just make one wonder what they look like.2. ArtworkGood quality. I enjoyed the graphics and the way the art comes alive in the animations. E.g. Bruno sleeping at the Circus.3. The Story TwistHeh... Not bad... I understand the meaning of the ""Whispered World"" now. In reflection, I think I won't leak any spoilers.CONS1. Too DifficultIt's nearly impossible to complete. You have to use Daedalic's Gameboomer walkthrough in order to finish it. How does one catch a rat with a sock? Or use a rat to save a pair of pants?2. Ridiculous StuffPicking pantaloons with rats? Oil from milking a cow? No conservation of mass? Some things just niggle at you in the wrong way due to how illogical it is.NEUTRAL1. Alternative EndingI couldn't be bothered to find it as the game was just too long."
