,Recommended,268540,34066744,Posted: 6 August,all,Menabugs,"The game starts off a little slow and unnecessarily complex, but once you kind of get in the groove of the game, it really picks up and is in the same realm of enjoyability as any Daedalic game. Of course, as most have pointed out, the main character's voice is the worst, so I muted the voices and game soundtrack about 2 min into the game and just listened to my own music. I don't know that I would be $20 for this game because the replay value to me is minimal since I disliked all the characters, but if you get it on sale, it's still a decent story with a really interesting ending."
